Taylor, maybe out in left field but I had a dry bearing issue on my 71 westy
in which the spindle really got hot and melted the rubber speedo sheath right
through the inner metal sheath and froze up the speedo cable. In doing so it
also rounded out the grease cap hole. On my 67 SC the grease cap hole was also
rounded out but I brazed it and filed it out square to match with a jewelers
file.

67 Single Cab, DP 1641cc 34 PICT-3
71 Trike 1776cc Dual T-4 34 PDSIT-3
VolksAir 1585cc 31 PICT
http://mywebpage.netscape.com/alphahr/case.html
Ray, Kent WA
